## 5ï¸âƒ£ Which Customers Generate Above-Average Sales?

### ğŸ”¹ Business Objective  
To segment high-performing customers.

### ğŸ”¹ Theoretical Insight  
Using a subquery, we compare individual customer sales with the average sales value.

Customers whose sales exceed the average are considered above-average contributors.

### ğŸ”¹ Business Impact  
- Target premium customer segment  
- Design exclusive campaigns  
- Identify characteristics of high-spending customers  
- Improve customer segmentation strategy  

---

## 6ï¸âƒ£ Which Products Are Making a Loss?

### ğŸ”¹ Business Objective  
To identify unprofitable products.

### ğŸ”¹ Theoretical Insight  
By grouping profit by product and filtering for negative profit, we identify loss-making products.

### ğŸ”¹ Business Impact  
- Review pricing strategy  
- Reduce production or supply costs  
- Discontinue non-performing products  
- Optimize discount structure  

This prevents revenue leakage and improves overall profitability.

